<br>
Being able to follow instructions is a requirement, but in order to get those instructions out we really need to cut back on needless chatter.<br>
<br>
For now I make the suggestion that Officers use some brackets to get the point across, like this:<br>
<br>
&lt;&lt;&lt;&lt;Everyone move up to me now&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;<br>
<br>
I also reccommend that everyone make use of the new /tt command where you can to accomplish things, for example I see that the officer in charge wants people to move back behind a certain place but their request is lost in the chatter, so I target one of the offenders and type /tt Move back please...    then I target the next offender and hit shift up-arrow return, repeat.  The tells are seen quickly and the officer gets support.<br>
<br>
I also would like everyone in the guild to send some /feedback:<br>
<br>
I have requested two new /gu features  /gshout and /ogu<br>
<br>
/gshout is a guild private shout chanel for all GUILD in the same zone<br>
<br>
/ogu is an OFFICER only broadcast to the guild serverwide in red that is similar to what I suggested before like this:<br>
<br>
&gt;&gt;&gt; Jaraan tells the Guild: TURTLE is up! get to IC now! &lt;&lt;&lt;<br>
<br>
PLEASE spend a few minutes to do a /feedback to see if we can get these in place. <p><IMG src="http://www.prattz.com/sig3.jpg"><Br>"I may not be the sharpest tool in the shed, but I REFUSE to be dull."  <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=68568">Magelo</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/usirtielyl.showPublicProfile?language=EN>sirtielyl</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Officer of Odysseys</span><br>  Posts: 414<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(2/7/02 2:52:50 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fodysseyxevfrm11.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=19.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.home.net/mmurad/images/tee_angb2.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Guild/Raid Communication</span><hr size=1> that would rule.<br>
