<br>
********<br>
<br>
Subj. Guild/Raid communications problem.<br>
<br>
I propose a solution to a big problem for the raids of Norrath: Communication. As a guild starts having more than 50 players at a raid they start to rely on /shout and /ooc to get the important communications through to the guild. If there are more than one guild in a zone this Pull/Panic spam begins to crossover to other guilds and it also can annoy the players in zone that are not part of the raid. Last night in Velks, 60 people went after Velkator, this was a pick-up raid that had LOTS of communication in /ooc and /shout and was MOST annoying to the other 40 people in the zone. As a solution to this, I propose three new channels/modes of communication.<br>
<br>
1) /gshout : This guild only shout channel shows up as red by default to all GUILD members in the same zone (can be turned off with the same guild chat filter) Would be nice with a leader and a trailer. EXAMPLE<br>
<br>
* Fenrik shouts to the guild: &quot;Camp a Cleric NOW!!&quot; *<br>
<br>
2) /ogu : Officer only channel that appears in red by default to all guild members on the server, preferrably with a leader and a trailer (can be turned off with the same guild chat filter) EXAMPLE<br>
<br>
&gt;&gt;&gt; Bob_Officer tells the guild: &quot;TURTLE is UP!!!   Get to IC NOW!!&quot; &lt;&lt;&lt;<br>
<br>
These two added features would allow for better communications within a guild at raids and alow for multiple guilds in the same zone to function without spaming each other in OOC or Shout, or for a guild to function while turning off OOC and Shout because of a pick-up raid going on in the same zone.<br>
<br>
3) /raid : This is an &quot;opt-in&quot; channel similar to /ooc and /shout and by default it is off with a switch like /raidchat on/off.   This channel is the same color as /ooc and would allow /ooc like broadcasts to all that are in the same zone and have that filter set. This would be a MAJOR benefit to the pick-up raid also allow for quieter zones where raids take place... <br>
<br>
Thank you for your time,<br>
<br>
Kaay Ess<br>
