<br>
Another thing, and most of you seem to follow this, however, self included, there are times I'm not as focused as i should be going into a raid. At our &quot;gathering spot&quot; prior to raid, everyone should be -consistent- in doing the following, without having to be told...<br>
<br>
1. Put LFG on<br>
2. Buff <br>
3. Shrink (when applicable)<br>
4. Adjust hot keys/macros for heals, assists, etc (if not permanent)<br>
5. Zip it &amp; listen<br>
<br>
Perhaps consistently designating one person in each group to do all the communication with the raid leader would help, too. Group leaders generally are clerics..they have enough to do as it is, so maybe the 2nd person down on the list. (?) This prevents the same question being asked repeatedly in guild, as well as spamming the leaders and officers. This includes buff requests and other info..MA, SA &lt;-- that has to be the most common asked question every 5 minutes...etc. <br>
<br>
Raids can be lengthy, and there are times I can feel my attention span slipping away, and i know i'm not the only one this is happening to. I'm open to doing whatever it takes to help our raids be smooth and succcessful. It's a rewarding feeling to set guidelines, follow through, and then see the results.<br>
